    desc:'An engineer finds a vulnerability that could have exposed user data, but no evidence of exploitation yet.',
    tag:'Security Event',
    correctSet:['sec','em','pm','cs'],
    primary:'sec',
    reasoning:"Security owns assessing the actual risk and containing it first, since acting too early or too publicly before understanding scope can cause unnecessary panic or tip off bad actors.",
    flow:['sec','em','pm','cs'],
    flowNote:"Security investigates and patches the vulnerability, engineering management coordinates the technical response, product manager decides on disclosure approach, and support is briefed in case customers ask."
  },
  {
